Based on the sorption results, the maximum sorption capacity of the 3D porous fluorescent hydrogel was computed by using a general method (Jiang et al., 2015; Zhou et al., 2016, 2018). As shown in Fig. 3
                        a, the maximum sorption capacities of FH-5 for Cr6+, Ba2+, Pb2+ and Cu2+ were 534.4, 271.9, 789.6 and 98.2 mg/g, respectively. This 3D porous fluorescent hydrogel has relatively larger adsorption capacities than those of other hydrogels published previously (Table 1
                        ). This result revealed that this 3D porous fluorescent hydrogel has an excellent sorption ability for heavy metals.
